**Root cause:** The backward scan in `close_orphaned_run_if_needed` returned `Ok(())` early whenever it found a `RunCompleted` (line 364) or a `RunStarted` that already had a `RunCompleted` (line 382). This meant the second pass (the new FailureObserved sweep) was never reached when a healthy completed run followed an orphaned one.

